docs.abstract: The justices heard arguments about whether to overrule a 1992 decision that shielded many internet retailers from having to collect sales taxes.
docs.snippet: The justices heard arguments about whether to overrule a 1992 decision that shielded many internet retailers from having to collect sales taxes.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A closely divided Supreme Court struggled on Tuesday to decide whether internet retailers should have to collect sales taxes in states where they have no physical presence.

headline.main: Supreme Court Divided on Sales Taxes for Online Purchases
headline.print_headline: Sales Taxes For Internet Split Court

docs.abstract: President Trump’s top trade adviser said his verbal attack against Canada’s prime minister was a “mistake.”
docs.snippet: President Trump’s top trade adviser said his verbal attack against Canada’s prime minister was a “mistake.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Peter Navarro, one of President Trump’s top trade advisers, said on Tuesday that it was a mistake to suggest that “there is a special place in hell” for Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada, offering a rare apology from a White House that almost never walks back heated rhetoric.

headline.main: Navarro Apologizes for ‘Special Place in Hell’ Comments About Trudeau
headline.print_headline: Trade Adviser Apologizes For His Slam on Trudeau

docs.abstract: President Trump’s school safety commission convened its first public hearing on Wednesday, and members got an earful from witnesses worried about its direction.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s school safety commission convened its first public hearing on Wednesday, and members got an earful from witnesses worried about its direction.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Students, parents and educators urged the federal officials charged with preventing the next school shooting to pour more mental health resources and school support staff into the nation’s elementary and secondary schools — not more guns.

headline.main: Witnesses Demand Focus on Guns at First School Safety Commission Hearing
headline.print_headline: Witnesses Beseech Panel on School Safety for Help

docs.abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo lifted the department’s hiring freeze in one of many efforts to restore the department’s effectiveness and morale.
docs.snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo lifted the department’s hiring freeze in one of many efforts to restore the department’s effectiveness and morale.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo announced on Tuesday that he was lifting the State Department’s hiring freeze, ending the Trump administration’s unpopular effort to slash funding and staffing levels for the United States’ diplomatic corps.

headline.main: Pompeo Lifts Hiring Freeze in Effort to Return ‘Swagger’ to State Dept.
headline.print_headline: After Nudge, Pompeo Lifts Hiring Freeze At State Dept.

docs.abstract: The first lady is at Walter Reed National Military Medical Center and is likely to remain there for the duration of the week.
docs.snippet: The first lady is at Walter Reed National Military Medical Center and is likely to remain there for the duration of the week.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Melania Trump underwent a medical procedure on Monday morning to treat what the White House called a “benign kidney condition” and was reported to be recovering without trouble at a military hospital outside the capital.

headline.main: Kidney Condition Puts Melania Trump in the Hospital
headline.print_headline: First Lady Is Hospitalized for Procedure to Correct ‘Benign Kidney Condition’

docs.abstract: The former officer, Kevin Mallory, faces life in prison, though his lawyers deny that he betrayed the United States.
docs.snippet: The former officer, Kevin Mallory, faces life in prison, though his lawyers deny that he betrayed the United States.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A former C.I.A. case officer faces life in prison after he was convicted on Friday of betraying his country to spy on behalf of China.

headline.main: Ex-C.I.A. Officer Is Convicted of Spying for China
headline.print_headline: Ex-C.I.A. Officer Convicted of Spying, and Faces Life

docs.abstract: The congressional watchdog found that the consultants pressured student borrowers to put their loans on ice, which allows borrowers to avoid default and schools to avoid losing federal funding.
docs.snippet: The congressional watchdog found that the consultants pressured student borrowers to put their loans on ice, which allows borrowers to avoid default and schools to avoid losing federal funding.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Colleges and universities are avoiding federal punishment for high student-loan default rates by hiring consultants who encourage borrowers to delay payments on their loans, even if that will cost them and taxpayers more in the long run, Congress’s nonpartisan watchdog found.

headline.main: Colleges Hire Consultants to Help Manipulate Student Loan Default Rates
headline.print_headline: Loophole Lets Colleges Mask Loan Default Rates Among Their Graduates

docs.abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said Wednesday that a diplomat stationed in Guangzhou, China, suffered the same ills as those attacked in Havana.
docs.snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said Wednesday that a diplomat stationed in Guangzhou, China, suffered the same ills as those attacked in Havana.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The same symptoms of a mysterious attack that sickened American diplomats in Cuba have been reported at a United States consulate in southern China, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told lawmakers on Wednesday.

headline.main: Pompeo Says Mysterious Sickness Among Diplomats in Cuba Has Spread to China

docs.abstract: The founding of Demand Justice, which aims to persuade liberals to approach judicial fights with the same passion as conservatives, comes as President Trump is focused on remaking the federal courts.
docs.snippet: The founding of Demand Justice, which aims to persuade liberals to approach judicial fights with the same passion as conservatives, comes as President Trump is focused on remaking the federal courts.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats learned the hard way in 2016 that the right is much more animated by judicial fights after Republicans’ refusal to consider the Supreme Court nomination of Merrick B. Garland helped rally conservative voters behind Donald J. Trump so he could fill a vacancy held open for nearly a year.

headline.main: After Garland Defeat, New Group Hopes to Draw Democrats to Judicial Battlefield
headline.print_headline: New Group Hopes To Lure Democrats To Judicial Fight

docs.abstract: F.B.I. and Justice Department officials have been quietly meeting with security researchers who have been working on approaches to provide such access to encrypted devices.
docs.snippet: F.B.I. and Justice Department officials have been quietly meeting with security researchers who have been working on approaches to provide such access to encrypted devices.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal law enforcement officials are renewing a push for a legal mandate that tech companies build tools into smartphones and other devices that would allow access to encrypted data in criminal investigations.

headline.main: Justice Dept. Revives Push to Mandate a Way to Unlock Phones
headline.print_headline: Justice Dept. Revives Push for Way to Crack Phones
